passages.text: Solid Execution Drives a Healthy Beat and Raise

Total revenue accelerated \(20\%\) y/y \((18\%)\) cc) with performance supported by acceleration of both Cloud and Self- Managed revenue. Total revenue was well ahead of the high end of the company's revenue guidance as well as consensus estimates. Embedded leverage in the model flowed through to better profitability and FCF as operating margins expanded 500bps y/y to \(15.7\%\) with FCF margins of \(25\%\) for the quarter. Outperformance was passed through to full year guidance as the increase to full year revenue guidance was greater than the magnitude of beat compared to guidance for 1Q. Guidance reflects macro conditions that didn't deteriorate as much as the company had initially feared. The company called out Gen AI related momentum in the quarter with traction as a runtime platform for building conversational AI and agentic applications. In addition to Gen AI, management cited platform consolidation as a meaningful tailwind during the quarter across Search, Observability, and Security. GTM changes the company implemented last year continue to bear fruit as the sales organization remains focused on expanding enterprise accounts and landing high- potential mid- market customers. We are encouraged by the healthy sales execution and ongoing innovation across Elastic's platform as the company continues to leverage its market position to capitalize on the convergence of Observability and Security. We remain Overweight rated as we increase our estimates and price target to reflect solid outperformance and improving outlook.

Strong 1Q results. Elastic reported strong 1Q results with total revenue of \(\) 415.3\mathrm{mm}(18\%\mathrm{y} / \mathrm{y}\mathrm{inCC}),\) and Cloud revenue of \(\) 195.8\mathrm{mm}(24\%\mathrm{y} / \mathrm{y}\mathrm{inCC}),\(both above consensus. ESTC saw broad- based strength in consumption and commitment, which was supported by demand for the Search AI platform and strong sales execution. Operating margin of \(15.7\%\) and FCF margin of \(25\%\) were above stg estimates. NRR remained stable at \(112\%\) . Management also highlighted stabilization in U.S. Public sector business.

Raised: FY guidance as macro stabilizes. ESTC increased its full year FY26 revenue outlook and reflected a lack of macro deterioration previously anticipated by management. Pricing increases for SaaS and Self- managed products during the quarter also supported the better outlook. The new revenue guidance of \(\) 1,679- 1,689\(implies\)14\%\(y/y growth or\)13\%\(y/y growth in constant currency at the mid- point. The company reiterated its FY26 operating margin guidance of\)16\%\(and noted that FY26 adjusted FCF margins will sustain the same levels achieved in FY25 (19.3\% margin).

secular trend for migration from incumbent legacy SIEM vendors to more modern, GenAI centric security solutions. ESTC highlighted that as AI reshapes the SIEM landscape, Elastic Security unifies SIEM and XDR into a single AI- powered platform, extending protection across customer data infrastructure and eliminating the need for multiple standalone tools. The company sees this as a multi- year opportunity and will focus on investing in security solutions that are more data- centric unlike Identity. Management also indicated that one- third of the security new and expansion deals in the quarter were competitive wins.

- Pricing changes announced in May. Elastic announced a price increase of approximately \(5\%\) on list prices across self-managed and SaaS solutions. Elastic regularly pursues these price increases, with the last being in 2024 but only for self-managed solutions. Management indicated that ESTC did not see a benefit from price increase in 1Q but that 2Q guidance factors in the price increases. The benefits of price increase are less noticeable sequentially and are more noticeable on a year-over-year basis. The company noted that price increases have not historically resulted in higher churn and, as the company innovates over time, customers are able to derive higher value from ESTC solutions, leading to price absorption.

Elastic (Overweight; Price Target: \(\) 120.00\$

While Elastic, at its core, is an open- source search technology, it offers a very powerful set of software products that enable it to ingest, filter, store, search, and analyze data in any form, whether structured or unstructured. This enables the stack to generate insights from a wide variety of data sources, driving the wide applicability of the Elastic platform across a broad range of use cases. The combination of the versatility of the platform along with its open- source model positions Elastic to disrupt multiple market segments within Enterprise IT, driving a \(\sim\) \(\) 45B\(TAM in aggregate, while enabling an efficient, largely inbound go- to- market model. We are impressed by Elastic's rapid growth profile, strong dollar- based net expansion rate, and superior sales efficiency. While the competitive environment continues to evolve, we believe the remarkable adaptability exhibited by Elastic's platform across different use cases will continue to distinguish it from others.

We establish our Dec 2026 price target of \(\) 120\(Prior: Dec - 25 PT of\) \ \(110\) is based on 6.5x EV/CY26E revenue (CY26E revenue \(=\) \ \(1,840mm). 6.5x CY26 revenue multiple is in- line with our sub - 20% growth coverage peers.

Security Breaches and Outages. Elastic provides some of its software over the internet, which involves transmission of its customers' data. Additionally, Elastic's applications are hosted, and the data are stored in third- party data centers. Any unauthorized access to the data due to security breaches or any outages that might impact the uptime of the systems could negatively impact Elastic's business.

Macroeconomic Gyrations. IT spending growth has remained positive for several years, but any macroeconomic headwinds could prompt buyers to more carefully consider their purchase or delay purchasing altogether, which could adversely affect Elastic.
